Police shot dead three suspected carjackers and recovered two pistols with six bullets on Wednesday in Nairobi.The three were gunned down following a carjacking incident on Kangundo road. Police said that the owner of the car, a female, was unhurt as police rescued her.The four suspected criminals, they said, had taken the woman hostage before a member of the public tipped off the police.The fourth suspect escaped on foot after the incident.Read: Two suspected thugs shot dead along Juja road, pistol recovered